item.title: Need help findin ip number for router
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

WINDOWSKEY + R. Then type in cmd. Now when cmd comes up, type in ipconfig. The “default gateway” is the IP address of your router (same IP you type into Internet Explorer/Firefox to view your router’s loging page.)
